<subSubSection pageId="35" pageNumber="36" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="35.[151,1436,1254,1495]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,1254,1279]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Pronotum with more or less distinctly carinate basal margin across middle one-fourth to one-half. Basal margin of elytra swollen, slightly to markedly costate from scutellum to, or almost to, humerus. Sclerotization of ventral surface of penis body broadly membranous. Endophallus lacking sclerites.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="35" pageNumber="36" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="35.[151,1436,1254,1495]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1362,1387]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Remarks.</emphasis>
